@nest-don can you provide a little more information?

- Is this a new project or existing project?
- Did this work in a previous version of either Android Studio or the Flutter plugin (prior to M41)?
- Does it repro in other Flutter project or with a newly created sample Flutter app?
- Would you mind upgrading to M42?  We haven't seen this problem before and I don't expect to see this magically fixed in M42 but I'd be curious if with the latest plugin you're still seeing the problem?

Thank you.
@terrylucas I don't think doOpenProject is the problem. I wonder what other plugins are installed?

macOS 10.15

It's an existing project.  This error was auto generated. 

> * Did this work in a previous version of either Android Studio or the Flutter plugin (prior to M41)?

I only started using Flutter recently. So everything is new.  The version I have is the first one I have used.

> * Does it repro in other Flutter project or with a newly created sample Flutter app?

No.

> * Would you mind upgrading to M42?  We haven't seen this problem before and I don't expect to see this magically fixed in M42 but I'd be curious if with the latest plugin you're still seeing the problem?

I will upgrade Andriod Studio 3.5.2 -> to 3.5.3.  
I will let you know if the problem persists.

> 
> Thank you.
Do you have any other plugins installed?

I have these plugins installed.
